pullsbody:
Fixes #15


As of January 1 2019, Mozilla requires that all GitHub projects include this [CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md](https://github.com/mozilla/repo-templates/blob/master/templates/CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md) file in the project root. The file has two parts:

1. Required Text - All text under the headings *Community Participation Guidelines and How to Report*, are required, and should not be altered.
2. Optional Text - The Project Specific Etiquette heading provides a space to speak more specifically about ways people can work effectively and inclusively together. Some examples of those can be found on the [Firefox Debugger](https://github.com/devtools-html/debugger.html/blob/master/CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md) project, and [Common Voice](https://github.com/mozilla/voice-web/blob/master/CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md). (The optional part is commented out in the [raw template file](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/mozilla/repo-templates/blob/master/templates/CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md), and will not be visible until you modify and uncomment that part.)

If you have any questions about this file, or Code of Conduct policies and procedures, please see [Mozilla-GitHub-Standards](https://wiki.mozilla.org/GitHub/Repository_Requirements) or email Mozilla-GitHub-Standards+CoC@mozilla.com.

_(Message COC002)_

pulltitle: Remove submodule and change to vendor for libaudit-go
pullsbody:
_Reason:_
Our current way of including `libaudit-go` as `./libaudit` is not the idiomatic _Go_ way to include external dependencies. We'll need to change to the standard way of using `github.com/mozilla/libaudit-go` so that `audit-go` supports the standard way of installing go programs using `go get` as our current way (`./libaudit`) will not work with `go get`.
Also we are using `libaudit-go` as a submodule which gives us the capability to develop `libaudit-go` separately and without breaking the current `audit-go` code and later when we are ready we can update `libaudit-go` to latest upstream. So it would now make sense to add it under `vendor/` which is introduced in [Go 1.5](https://blog.gopheracademy.com/advent-2015/vendor-folder/). This way we can continue to work in similar work fashion as we used to have under git submodule.
Further to maintain external dependencies for audit-go (which currently is only `libaudit-go`) we can use [Godep](https://github.com/tools/godep) which is provided by the standard golang community.
pull_repo_desc: Linux Audit Plugin for heka written using netlink Protocol in golang and Lua
pull_commit_message:
Remove submodule and change to vendor for libaudit-go
Changed path for json files required by libaudit-go

Reason: Standard way of installing go programs is by "go get" and our way of
using "./libaudit.go" wouldn't work with "go get" and also it wasn't a
recommended way to structure go packages. One way or another we would have
to revert to standard method. Since we were using libaudit as a submodule
it would now make sense to add it under "vendor/" as many go-packages are
doing today. We can continue to work in similar work fashion as we used to
have under git submodule and can update libaudit-go to upstream only when
we are ready.
